<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11570&amp;p=133016#p133016</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11570&amp;p=133016#p133016"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NES controller for Famicom]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11570&amp;p=133016#p133016"><![CDATA[
You can make (or buy) a connector for the expansion port on the front of the Famicom that you can connect two NES controllers to. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GXuxNjXNKkw" class="postlink">Here's what mine looks like</a>. That way you don't have to destroy any original parts.<br /><br />Yes, the controllers are compatible, they use the same set of connections for either the Famicom or NES, though obviously the NES second controller can't produce the microphone signal.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Sun Aug 24, 2014 11:16 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
